leads.lead_text: Inflorescences cylindric, the flowers pointing in all directions, often cream, rarely yellow; branching at ground-level and, at least in the form of axillary vegetative buds, in upper parts
Inflorescences unilateral (at least in lower part), the mature flowers pointed to one side, pale to deep yellow; branching at ground-level only
